cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CC 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it introduces a new relaxation of Differential Privacy, which is a concept closely related to privacy and security. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as Differential Privacy is often used in the context of machine learning. Additionally, the paper's focus on accuracy could make it relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper's potential applications in distributed computing could make it relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
